Articles from Britannica encyclopedias for elementary and high school students.Robert Borden - Children's Encyclopedia (Ages 8-11)(1854-1937). Robert Borden was the prime minister of Canada during World War I. He helped Canada gain greater independence from Great Britain.Robert Laird Borden - Student Encyclopedia (Ages 11 and up)(1854-1937). A statesman who helped transform Canada from a colony into a nation, Robert Laird Borden was Canada’s prime minister during World War I. Borden’s commitment to an international role for Canada was largely responsible for the government’s vigorous war measures, including a policy of conscription, during those years. He was also the first minister of a British overseas dominion to serve as a member of the Imperial War Cabinet of Great Britain (1917-19).
